{
  "version": 3,
  "tag_vocabulary": {
    "mood": ["anxious", "wired", "flat", "sad", "frustrated", "scattered", "overwhelmed"],
    "need": ["grounding", "calming", "focusing", "energizing", "perspective", "self-compassion"],
    "context": ["morning", "late-night", "pre-task", "post-conflict"],
    "ring": ["earth", "water", "fire", "wind", "void"]
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "q-01",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "You have power over your mind — not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength.",
      "attribution": "Marcus Aurelius",
      "tags": ["overwhelmed", "frustrated", "perspective", "grounding", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-02",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Between stimulus and response there is a space. In that space is our power to choose our response.",
      "attribution": "Viktor Frankl",
      "tags": ["frustrated", "wired", "post-conflict", "perspective", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-03",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "He who has a why to live for can bear almost any how.",
      "attribution": "Friedrich Nietzsche",
      "tags": ["flat", "sad", "overwhelmed", "perspective", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-04",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "The obstacle in the path becomes the path. Never forget, within every obstacle is an opportunity to improve our condition.",
      "attribution": "Ryan Holiday",
      "tags": ["frustrated", "overwhelmed", "perspective", "pre-task", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-05",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "You cannot stop the waves, but you can learn to surf.",
      "attribution": "Jon Kabat-Zinn",
      "tags": ["anxious", "overwhelmed", "calming", "perspective", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-06",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "What we do now echoes in eternity.",
      "attribution": "Marcus Aurelius",
      "tags": ["flat", "energizing", "pre-task", "perspective", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-07",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "We suffer more often in imagination than in reality.",
      "attribution": "Seneca",
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "perspective", "calming", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-08",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "If you are distressed by anything external, the pain is not due to the thing itself, but to your estimate of it; and this you have the power to revoke at any moment.",
      "attribution": "Marcus Aurelius",
      "tags": ["frustrated", "post-conflict", "perspective", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-09",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "You are the sky. Everything else — it's just the weather.",
      "attribution": "Pema Chödrön",
      "tags": ["sad", "overwhelmed", "anxious", "perspective", "self-compassion", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-10",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "First, say to yourself what you would be; and then do what you have to do.",
      "attribution": "Epictetus",
      "tags": ["scattered", "flat", "focusing", "pre-task", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-11",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Do not pray for an easy life, pray for the strength to endure a difficult one.",
      "attribution": "Bruce Lee",
      "tags": ["overwhelmed", "sad", "energizing", "perspective", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "q-12",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "The wound is the place where the Light enters you.",
      "attribution": "Rumi",
      "tags": ["sad", "self-compassion", "perspective", "late-night", "void"]
    },

    {
      "id": "m-01",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Do nothing which is of no use.",
      "attribution": "Miyamoto Musashi",
      "tags": ["scattered", "frustrated", "focusing", "pre-task", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "m-02",
      "type": "quote",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "From one thing, know ten thousand things.",
      "attribution": "Miyamoto Musashi",
      "tags": ["scattered", "overwhelmed", "perspective", "focusing", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "m-03",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Foundation first. Feel the floor under you, the chair against your back, the breath in your chest. You don't need to see the whole path. You only need to know where you're standing right now. Build from there.",
      "attribution": "Earth — foundation",
      "tags": ["anxious", "scattered", "overwhelmed", "grounding", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "m-04",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Don't fight the current of this. Let it move through you the way water moves around a stone. You are the stone. The feeling is the water. It will pass. You will still be here.",
      "attribution": "Water — flow",
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "overwhelmed", "calming", "self-compassion", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "m-05",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Step outside the version of this you've been telling yourself. What would a stranger see? What would someone you respect say? Other schools of seeing exist. The story you have isn't the only one.",
      "attribution": "Wind — other ways",
      "tags": ["frustrated", "overwhelmed", "post-conflict", "perspective", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "m-06",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Sit. Eyes open or closed — your call. Let the next 60 seconds be empty. No fixing, no thinking, no doing. When thoughts come, let them come and go like clouds. The space underneath them has always been here. Always will be.",
      "attribution": "Void — empty space",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["anxious", "overwhelmed", "late-night", "self-compassion", "void"]
    },

    {
      "id": "g-01",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "5–4–3–2–1. Look around and name 5 things you can see. Then 4 things you can feel touching your body. Then 3 things you can hear. Then 2 things you can smell. Then 1 thing you can taste. Take it slow — the point is the noticing.",
      "attribution": "5-4-3-2-1 senses",
      "duration_sec": 120,
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "scattered", "overwhelmed", "grounding", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-02",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Feet on the floor. Press them down. Feel the ground holding you up — it has been doing that this whole time. Notice the weight of your body in the chair, the temperature of the air, the back of your shirt against your skin. You are here. You are held.",
      "attribution": "Feet-on-floor",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["anxious", "overwhelmed", "scattered", "grounding", "self-compassion", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-03",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Body scan, top down. Forehead — soften it. Jaw — unclench. Shoulders — drop them an inch. Chest — let it open. Belly — let it be soft. Hands — unfurl them. Notice anywhere you were holding tension you didn't know about.",
      "attribution": "Top-down body scan",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["wired", "anxious", "overwhelmed", "calming", "grounding", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-04",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Name it to tame it. Out loud or in your head: \"I'm noticing anxiety. I'm noticing a tight chest. I'm noticing the thought that I'm going to fail.\" Naming the experience moves it from the driver's seat to the passenger seat.",
      "attribution": "Affect labeling",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["anxious", "frustrated", "overwhelmed", "scattered", "grounding", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-05",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Orient. Slowly turn your head left, then right, then up, then down. Let your eyes wander to whatever they want to land on. This signals your nervous system that you're safe in your environment — it's a built-in reset.",
      "attribution": "Orienting",
      "duration_sec": 45,
      "tags": ["wired", "anxious", "scattered", "grounding", "calming", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-06",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Cold water reset. Splash cold water on your face, or hold an ice cube in your palm for 30 seconds, or run wrists under cold tap. The cold triggers the dive reflex — heart rate drops, parasympathetic kicks in. Fastest physiological reset there is.",
      "attribution": "Mammalian dive reflex",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["wired", "anxious", "overwhelmed", "grounding", "calming", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "g-07",
      "type": "grounding",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Hand on heart. Place one hand on your chest, the other on your belly. Feel the rise and fall. Say to yourself: \"This is a moment of suffering. Suffering is part of being human. May I be kind to myself right now.\"",
      "attribution": "Self-compassion break (Kristin Neff)",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["sad", "overwhelmed", "self-compassion", "grounding", "late-night", "void"]
    },

    {
      "id": "b-01",
      "type": "breath",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Box breathing. Inhale 4 → hold 4 → exhale 4 → hold 4. Repeat for 8 rounds. Used by Navy SEALs to calm down before high-stakes moments.",
      "attribution": "Box breathing (4-4-4-4)",
      "duration_sec": 120,
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "pre-task", "calming", "focusing", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "b-02",
      "type": "breath",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "4-7-8. Inhale through nose for 4. Hold for 7. Exhale slowly through mouth for 8. Repeat 4 times. The long exhale is the active ingredient — it tells your nervous system the threat has passed.",
      "attribution": "4-7-8 breath (Andrew Weil)",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "overwhelmed", "late-night", "calming", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "b-03",
      "type": "breath",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Physiological sigh. Two quick inhales through your nose (a big one, then a small top-up), then one long slow exhale through your mouth. Repeat 1–3 times. Fastest way to lower stress in real time — works in under 30 seconds.",
      "attribution": "Physiological sigh (Huberman / Feldman)",
      "duration_sec": 30,
      "tags": ["anxious", "wired", "overwhelmed", "frustrated", "calming", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "b-04",
      "type": "breath",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Coherent breathing. Inhale 5, exhale 5. Just that. Five rounds. Brings heart rate variability up and signals safety to your nervous system. The simplest breath practice that exists.",
      "attribution": "Coherent / resonance breathing",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["scattered", "anxious", "calming", "focusing", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "b-05",
      "type": "breath",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Extended exhale. Inhale through your nose for a count of 4. Exhale through your nose or pursed lips for a count of 8. Whatever the inhale is, double the exhale. Six rounds.",
      "attribution": "Extended exhale",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["wired", "anxious", "overwhelmed", "calming", "water"]
    },

    {
      "id": "r-01",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "What would you tell a friend who was feeling exactly this right now? Now — say that to yourself. You're allowed to be on your own side.",
      "attribution": "Self-compassion reframe",
      "tags": ["sad", "overwhelmed", "frustrated", "self-compassion", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-02",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Will this matter in 10 minutes? In 10 days? In 10 months? In 10 years? Most things scale down quickly when you zoom out.",
      "attribution": "10-10-10 zoom-out",
      "tags": ["anxious", "frustrated", "overwhelmed", "perspective", "wind"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-03",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Two columns: what's in my control, what's not. Anything in the second column — set it down, just for now. You can pick it up later if you want. Right now, only act on column one.",
      "attribution": "Dichotomy of control",
      "tags": ["anxious", "overwhelmed", "scattered", "frustrated", "focusing", "perspective", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-04",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "You are not your thoughts. Try this: \"I am having the thought that I am failing.\" Notice the gap that opens up. The thought is a passenger. You're the one driving.",
      "attribution": "Cognitive defusion (ACT)",
      "tags": ["anxious", "sad", "overwhelmed", "perspective", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-05",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "What would the version of me I'm trying to become do in this moment? Don't think about who you are. Think about who you're becoming. Act from there.",
      "attribution": "Future-self reframe",
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "pre-task", "energizing", "perspective", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-06",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Name three values that matter to you. Just three. Now: which of them does the next 10 minutes serve? You don't need to feel motivated. You need to act in line with what you care about.",
      "attribution": "Values check",
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "pre-task", "focusing", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-07",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "This feeling will not last. It never has. Sit with it the way you'd sit with a friend who's having a hard time. You don't have to fix it. You just have to be there.",
      "attribution": "Impermanence",
      "tags": ["sad", "overwhelmed", "anxious", "self-compassion", "late-night", "water"]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-08",
      "type": "reframe",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "What is this feeling actually trying to tell me? Anger often points to a violated value. Anxiety often points to something I care about. Sadness often points to something I've lost. Listen before you try to make it go away.",
      "attribution": "Emotion as information",
      "tags": ["frustrated", "sad", "anxious", "post-conflict", "perspective", "wind"]
    },

    {
      "id": "a-01",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Stand up. Walk outside, even if it's just to the front step or window. 60 seconds of fresh air and a different visual field. That's the whole assignment.",
      "attribution": "60-second outside",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "overwhelmed", "energizing", "morning", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-02",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Drink a full glass of water. Slowly. Notice the temperature, the swallow, the breath after. Most low-energy moments have a dehydration component.",
      "attribution": "Hydrate + notice",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "morning", "energizing", "grounding", "earth"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-03",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "10 pushups. Or 20 air squats. Or 30 jumping jacks. Pick one. Do it now. Movement is the fastest legal mood-changer there is.",
      "attribution": "Movement reset",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "wired", "energizing", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-04",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Write one sentence — just one — about how you're actually feeling right now. No editing. No audience. Then close the app. The act of putting it into words is the medicine.",
      "attribution": "One-sentence journal",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["sad", "overwhelmed", "scattered", "anxious", "self-compassion", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-05",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Text one person who matters to you. \"Thinking of you\" is enough. You're allowed to need connection. They're allowed to want to hear from you.",
      "attribution": "Reach out",
      "duration_sec": 60,
      "tags": ["sad", "flat", "self-compassion", "late-night", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-06",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Tidy one thing. One. The corner of the desk, the bedside table, the coffee mug. Action precedes motivation — the small win opens the door.",
      "attribution": "Tidy one thing",
      "duration_sec": 120,
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "overwhelmed", "energizing", "focusing", "fire"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-07",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Record a 30-second voice memo to yourself. Talk through what's going on. Then play it back. Hearing your own voice say the thing changes its weight.",
      "attribution": "Voice memo to self",
      "duration_sec": 90,
      "tags": ["overwhelmed", "scattered", "sad", "self-compassion", "void"]
    },
    {
      "id": "a-08",
      "type": "action",
      "source_type": "curated",
      "text": "Sunlight on your face for 2 minutes. If it's daytime, go to a window or step outside. If it's not, switch on a bright light and look at something 6+ feet away. Light entrains the system.",
      "attribution": "Light exposure",
      "duration_sec": 120,
      "tags": ["flat", "scattered", "morning", "energizing", "fire"]
    },
